ion start** (`handleLifecycleSessionStart` in `lifecycle.go:92`) — already writes the \\\"Powered by Entire\\\" banner via `WriteHookResponse`. This was the only hook that *would have* produced output once `HookResponseWriter` existed.\\n2. **TurnStart/TurnEnd** — these lifecycle handlers don't call `WriteHookResponse`, but they return to `hook_registry.go` with `hookErr == nil`, which doesn't trigger the new no-op ack. However, since they produce *lifecycle events* (non-nil), they go through `DispatchLifecycleEvent` which does its work and returns. The Kiro IDE already gets output from the \\\"Powered by Entire\\\" banner on the first `promptSubmit` (which maps to SessionStart via the session-start-as-first-prompt fallback pattern).\\n3. **No-op hooks** (`preToolUse`/`postToolUse`) — these return `nil` events from `ParseHookEvent`, so they never reach the lifecycle dispatcher. The new code in `hook_registry.go:153-158` catches these and writes a minimal ack.\\n`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`\\n\\nAll done. Here's a summary of the changes:\\n\\n### Changes Made\\n\\n**1. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/lifecycle.go`** — Added `HookResponseWriter` implementation:\\n- Compile-time interface assertion `var _ agent.HookResponseWriter = (*KiroAgent)(nil)`\\n- `WriteHookResponse()` method that writes plain text to stdout via `fmt.Fprintln` (matching Factory AI Droid's pattern)\\n\\n**2. `cmd/entire/cli/hook_registry.go`** — Added no-op hook acknowledgment:\\n- When a hook returns `nil` event (preToolUse/postToolUse) and the agent implements `HookResponseWriter`, writes an empty ack to stdout\\n- This prevents the Kiro IDE from timing out on pass-through hooks\\n\\n**3. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/lifecycle_test.go`** — Added tests:\\n- `TestWriteHookResponse` — verifies message is written to stdout with trailing newline\\n- `TestWriteHookResponse_EmptyMessage` — verifies empty string still produces `\\\\n` (the minimal ack)\\n- `captureStdout` helper for stdout capture in tests\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":109,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":120794,\"output_tokens\":665,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":109,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYiahV3fN4uLE1aQ53xMH\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"8c550b33-91d9-4065-af65-80f82fc46015\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T19:20:45.574Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"8c550b33-91d9-4065-af65-80f82fc46015\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"85674590-7374-4682-8632-6db336ae1ea0\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"snazzy-dreaming-badger\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"Stop\",\"hookName\":\"Stop\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"66c5d6f4-9bed-424b-a43f-620a3fa5b6e3\",\"toolUseID\":\"66c5d6f4-9bed-424b-a43f-620a3fa5b6e3\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T19:20:45.604Z\",\"uuid\":\"f10a1fa1-1221-4992-8b76-3a6507a56c2a\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"f10a1fa1-1221-4992-8b76-3a6507a56c2a\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"85674590-7374-4682-8632-6db336ae1ea0\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"snazzy-dreaming-badger\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"Stop\",\"hookName\":\"Stop\",\"command\":\"cmux claude-hook stop\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"66c5d6f4-9bed-424b-a43f-620a3fa5b6e3\",\"toolUseID\":\"66c5d6f4-9bed-424b-a43f-620a3fa5b6e3\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T19:20:45.604Z\",\"uuid\":\"56842297-d936-4867-97a3-4bf180b226e3\"}\n{\"par